te via `python3 <file>` using `execute_command()`\n146:   - Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n147:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n148:   - Verify: Python code executes correctly\n149: \n150: - [x] **T3.6** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.write_file()`\n151:   - Parameters: `content: str`, `remote_path: str`\n152:   - Base64 encode content\n153:   - POST JSON to `api/files`: `path`, `content`, `mode=\"0644\"`\n154:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n155:   - Verify: File created via base64 encoding\n156: \n157: - [x] **T3.7** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file()`\n158:   - Parameters: `local_path: str`, `remote_path: str`\n159:   - Read local file as binary\n160:   - POST multipart to `api/files` with `file`, `path`, `mode`\n161:   - Set `x-agentcube-session-id` header explicitly\n162:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n163:   - Verify: Multipart upload succeeds\n164: \n165: - [x] **T3.8** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.download_file()`\n166:   - Parameters: `remote_path: str`, `local_path: str`\n167:   - Clean path: `remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n168:   - GET from `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True`\n169:   - Write chunks to local file\n170:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n171:   - Verify: File downloaded correctly\n172: \n173: - [x] **T3.9** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.list_files()`\n174:   - Parameter: `path: str = \".\"`\n175:   - GET from `api/files` with query `path`\n176:   - Return JSON response\n177:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n178:   - Verify: Returns file list\n179: \n180: - [x] **T3.10** Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.close()`\n181:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n182:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n183:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n184: \n185: - [x] **T3.11** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n186:   - Import `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`, dependencies\n187:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n188:   - Verify: Module structure correct\n189: \n190: - [x] **T3.12** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__()`\n191:   - Parameters: `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n192:   - Compute `base_url` from `router_url` + namespace + agent_name path using `urljoin()`\n193:   - Create session with `create_session()`\n194:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n195:   - Verify: Base URL computed correctly, connection pool configured (10/10)\n196: \n197: - [x] **T3.13** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()`\n198:   - GET from `self.base_url`\n199:   - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n200:   - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n201:   - Return session ID\n202:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n203:   - Verify: Extracts session ID from response header\n204: \n205: - [x] **T3.14** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()`\n206:   - Parameters: `session_id`, `payload: Dict[str, Any]`, `timeout: Optional[float]`\n207:   - Set headers: `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json`\n208:   - Apply timeout: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` or instance default\n209:   - POST JSON payload to `self.base_url`\n210:   - Return `requests.Response`\n211:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n212:   - Verify: Request sent with correct headers and timeout\n213: \n214: - [x] **T3.15** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.close()`\n215:   - Call `self.session.close()`\n216:   - File: `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n217:   - Verify: HTTP session closed\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Phase 4: Configura