mandExecutionError`, placeholders)\n436: 5. ✅ Environment variable resolution works (`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n437: 6. ✅ Unit tests cover all scenarios (HTTP timeout, pool reuse, error cases)\n438: 7. ✅ Session header uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`\n439: 8. ✅ Read timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to command execution\n440: 9. ✅ Control plane handles 404 as idempotent success on delete\n441: 10. ✅ Data plane init failure triggers cleanup and re-raise\n442: 11. ✅ Router URL validation: `ValueError` if both arg and env missing\n443: 12. ✅ Bootstrap session ID from Router invocation endpoint\n444: 13. ✅ Per-call timeout override supported\n445: 14. ✅ `urljoin()` used for relative path building\n446: 15. ✅ All clients implement context manager protocol\n447: 16. ✅ Logging configured with verbose option\n448: 17. ✅ Package exports: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n449: 18. ✅ Clients export: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, ...`\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: **Notes:**\n454: - Stage ST-3 marked complete: all HTTP clients and infrastructure implemented\n455: - Session header naming: uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` throughout\n456: - Timeout handling: read timeout gets +2.0s buffer for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`\n457: - Exception usage: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core clients (reserved for future expansion)\n458: - Distributed configuration: no single `Configuration` class; each client resolves own settings from args/env\n459: - Connection pooling: all clients use `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` by default\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端 Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Package Structure & Utilities ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1** Create `agentcube/__init__.py`\n  - Import `CodeInterprete